Allow us to introduce you to <b>Elizabeth</b>, our featured citizen of the week!<br><br>Elizabeth is both smart and outgoing. She also shows her compassionate side by volunteering for the Peabody Park Clean-Up. Her interest in Math probably helped her out in winning her shiny Sudoku trophy. Foreign Language skills also come in handy when you're communicating to far away life forms while saving the galaxy in Galactic Defender <br><br>Hanging out at the Football Game has probably helped Elizabeth work on her fundamental football skills. From the looks of her polished Tricky Touchdown trophy, this seems to have paid off. She also has trophies for Sink Three, Hop and Drop, and Home Run Derby. <br><br>Elizabeth moved to Millsberry on June 12, 2006. Since then she's been hanging in her Ravenwood home at <a href='/home/?user=peapickr'>8090 Barclay Road</a>. If you're afraid of heights, you may want to make note that Elizabeth's house is a towering three stories high. You can always keep things at a low altitude by hanging out in Elizabeth's "Patch of Aloneness" garden where you'll find an ode to Cupid. <br><br>If action is more your thing, you'll feel right at home in Elizabeth's "Arcade of Games". Here you have the option of playing Elizabeth's vintage dome hockey game. There are also regulation hockey goals and sticks if you happen to prefer a more life-size experience. <br><br>When you see Elizabeth, be sure to congratulate her on being our featured citizen. <br><br></div>
